# TeamOfTen — example environment file.
#
# Only env vars that the operator actually configures per deploy live
# here. Everything else has either a Dockerfile-baked value or a code
# default that you typically don't tune.
#
# What is NOT here:
#   - CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR / CODEX_HOME — set in the Dockerfile
#     (/data/claude, /data/codex). Override only if your volume mount
#     differs from the standard layout.
#   - Project repo URL + branch — configured per project (Projects
#     pane); the legacy single-project HARNESS_PROJECT_REPO env var
#     is gone.
#   - External MCP servers — Options drawer → MCP servers, with
#     credentials in the encrypted secrets store.
#   - Coach recurring tick — runtime via `/tick N` slash or
#     `PUT /api/coach/tick`; writes to the `coach_recurrence` table.
#   - Data paths (HARNESS_DATA_ROOT, HARNESS_WORKSPACES_ROOT,
#     HARNESS_DB_PATH, HARNESS_OUTPUTS_DIR, etc.) — defaulted in code
#     under /data and /workspaces. See server/paths.py +
#     server/workspaces.py if you need to override.
#   - Tuning knobs (retention, sync intervals, auto-compact threshold,
#     auto-wake debounce, error-retry timing, stale-task watchdog,
#     handoff token budget, event batching). All have sensible
#     defaults. Search server/ for `os.environ.get("HARNESS_` if
#     you need to tune one.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------
# Auth — required when the URL is public
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------

# Bearer token required on every /api/* request (except /api/health)
# and on the WebSocket as ?token=. If unset, the API is open — fine
# for localhost, not OK on a public URL.
HARNESS_TOKEN=

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------
# WebDAV mirror — required for the kDrive / Nextcloud backup
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------

# Works with any WebDAV-compatible cloud drive: Infomaniak kDrive,
# Nextcloud, ownCloud, Fastmail Files, etc. All three must be set
# or the mirror stays disabled (the app still works, writes just
# live on the local volume only).
HARNESS_WEBDAV_URL=
HARNESS_WEBDAV_USER=
HARNESS_WEBDAV_PASSWORD=

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------
# Cost caps — recommended (defaults are 5 / 20 USD/day)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------

# Per-Player daily limit. Agent won't spawn if today's spend ≥ this.
HARNESS_AGENT_DAILY_CAP=5.0
# Whole-team daily limit. Overrides per-Player when hit.
HARNESS_TEAM_DAILY_CAP=20.0

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------
# Codex runtime feature gate
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------

# When unset/false, the UI can show Codex auth status but the API
# rejects runtime=codex. Set to `true` to enable per-slot Codex
# selection. Then run inside the container:
#   codex login --device-auth
HARNESS_CODEX_ENABLED=true

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------
# Encrypted secrets store — required for Telegram + MCP credentials
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------

# Fernet master key for the secrets table (44-char urlsafe-base64).
# Generate via:
#   python -c "from cryptography.fernet import Fernet; print(Fernet.generate_key().decode())"
# Required if you want to manage MCP server credentials or the
# Telegram bot token from the Options drawer (rather than env vars).
HARNESS_SECRETS_KEY=

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------
# Telegram bridge — first-boot bootstrap only (UI takes over after)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------

# Optional first-boot values. Once you save them in Options →
# Telegram bridge they persist in the encrypted secrets store and
# the env vars are ignored.
# Token format: <bot_id>:<auth_token> from BotFather.
# Chat IDs: comma-separated numeric ids of allowed chats. Without a
# whitelist the bridge refuses to start.
TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=
TELEGRAM_ALLOWED_CHAT_IDS=
